sentences: Thérèse Brenet (born 22 October 1935) is a French composer.
Born in Paris, she studied at the Conservatoire de Reims and since 1954 the Conservatoire de Paris.
In 1965 she won the Prix de Rome for her Les Visions prophétiques de Cassandre; a prize which enabled her to pursue further studies at the French Academy in Rome.
